<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
	<head>
		<meta charset="UTF-8" />
		<meta http-equiv="X-UA-Compatible" content="IE=edge" />
		<meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />
		<title>CPD Log</title>
		<link
			rel="stylesheet"
			href="https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/font-awesome/6.2.0/css/all.min.css"
		/>
		<link
			href="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/bootstrap@5.2.1/dist/css/bootstrap.min.css"
			rel="stylesheet"
			integrity="sha384-iYQeCzEYFbKjA/T2uDLTpkwGzCiq6soy8tYaI1GyVh/UjpbCx/TYkiZhlZB6+fzT"
			crossorigin="anonymous"
		/>
	</head>
	<body>
		<section class="row container">
			<h1>CPD LOG</h1>
			<p class="col">
				CMI members <em>(Chartered Managers Institute) </em>are required to make
				a commitment to their ongoing professional development and learning
			</p>
			<p class="col">
				Keeping a CPD Log
				<em>(Continuing Professional Development)</em>
				helps a leader to identify and reflect on learning opportunities in
				their day to day work.
			</p>
			<p class="col">
				This CPD app supports managers in that activity, providing a simple,
				structured method for adding, deleting and reviewing past log entries.
			</p>
			<p class="col">
				The act of recalling, reflecting and reasoning through them can cement
				them in your mind to help your learning and development as a leader.
			</p>
			<p class="col">
				CPD reflections typically make great case studies for behavioural
				recruitment questions and reflecting can help you interview better.
			</p>
			<form class="row gx-5 container" action="/addEntry" method="POST">
				<input type="text" placeholder="Short summary" name="summary" />
				<input type="date" name="date" />
				<input type="text" placeholder="what happened?" name="cause" />
				<input type="text" placeholder="what did you do?" name="action" />
				<input type="text" placeholder="How did it go?" name="result" />
				<input type="text" placeholder="What did you learn?" name="learned" />
				<input class="btn btn-primary" type="submit" />
			</form>
		</section>
		<br />
		<section class="row container">
			<h2>Log Entries</h2>
			<!-- takes the provided entries data and loops over it.-->
			<div class="accordion" id="accordionEntry">
				<% for (let i=0; i < entries.length; i++) { %>
				<div class="accordion-item">
					<h2 class="accordion-header" id="heading<%=i%>">
						<button
							class="accordion-button collapsed"
							type="button"
							data-bs-toggle="collapse"
							data-bs-target="#collapse<%=i%>"
							aria-expanded="false"
							aria-controls="collapse<%=i%>"
						>
							<span><%= entries[i].summary %></span>
							<span>&nbsp;<%= entries[i].date %>&nbsp;</span>
							<span class="fas fa-trash"></span>
						</button>
					</h2>

					<div
						id="collapse<%=i%>"
						class="accordion-collapse collapse"
						aria-labelledby="heading<%=i%>"
					>
						<div class="accordion-body">
							<span><strong>Cause: </strong></span>
							<p><%= entries[i].cause %></p>
							<span><strong>Action: </strong></span>
							<p><%= entries[i].action %></p>
							<span><strong>Result: </strong></span>
							<p><%= entries[i].result %></p>
							<span><strong>What I Learned: </strong></span>
							<p><%= entries[i].learned %></p>
						</div>
					</div>
				</div>
				<% } %>
			</div>
		</section>
		<script src="js/main.js"></script>
		<script
			src="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/bootstrap@5.2.1/dist/js/bootstrap.bundle.min.js"
			integrity="sha384-u1OknCvxWvY5kfmNBILK2hRnQC3Pr17a+RTT6rIHI7NnikvbZlHgTPOOmMi466C8"
			crossorigin="anonymous"
		></script>
	</body>
</html>
